    Task#

    pyticktick.models.v2.parameters.task #

    Parameters for creating and updating tasks via the V2 API.

    Unofficial API

    These models are part of the unofficial TickTick API. They were created by reverse engineering the API. They may be incomplete or inaccurate.

    Classes:

    Name Description
    CreateItemV2

    Model for creating a checklist item via the V2 API.
    CreateTaskReminderV2

    Model for creating a reminder for a task via the V2 API.
    CreateTaskV2

    Model for creating a task via the V2 API.
    DeleteTaskV2

    Model for deleting a task via the V2 API.
    PostBatchTaskV2

    Model for batch task operations via the V2 API.
    UpdateItemV2

    Model for updating a checklist item via the V2 API.
    UpdateTaskReminderV2

    Model for creating a reminder for a task via the V2 API.
    UpdateTaskV2

    Model for updating a task via the V2 API.

    CreateItemV2 pydantic-model #

    Bases: BaseModelV2

    Model for creating a checklist item via the V2 API.

    This model is used to create a checklist item via the V2 API, but its identical to the CreateItemV1 model. It directly maps to the 'items' field in the create task documentation. It is used in the CreateTaskV2 model.

    Convert empty strings to None.

    @field_validator("*", mode="before")
@classmethod
def empty_str_to_none(cls, v: Any) -> Any:
    """Convert empty strings to None.

    TickTick API responses sometimes conflates `None` and empty strings for
    optional fields. This validator ensures that empty strings are converted to
    `None`, which then allows for more consistent handling of the data within the
    library.

    Args:
        v (Any): The value to validate.

    Returns:
        Any: The input value if it is not an empty string, otherwise `None`.
    """
    if isinstance(v, str) and len(v) == 0:
        return None
    return v

    CreateTaskV2 pydantic-model #

    Bases: BaseModelV2

    Model for creating a task via the V2 API.

    This model is used to create a task via the V2 API. It mostly maps to the 'items' field in the create task documentation. The main differences are the addition of the following fields:

    • modified_time
    • completed_time
    • completed_user_id
    • tags
    • etag
    • kind
    • status
    • is_floating
    • creator
    • assignee
    • progress

    @field_validator("*", mode="before")
@classmethod
def empty_str_to_none(cls, v: Any) -> Any:
    """Convert empty strings to None.

    TickTick API responses sometimes conflates `None` and empty strings for
    optional fields. This validator ensures that empty strings are converted to
    `None`, which then allows for more consistent handling of the data within the
    library.

    Args:
        v (Any): The value to validate.

    Returns:
        Any: The input value if it is not an empty string, otherwise `None`.
    """
    if isinstance(v, str) and len(v) == 0:
        return None
    return v

    empty_str_to_none(v: Any) -> Any

    Convert empty strings to None.

    TickTick API responses sometimes conflates None and empty strings for optional fields. This validator ensures that empty strings are converted to None, which then allows for more consistent handling of the data within the library.

    Parameters:

    Name Type Description Default
    v Any

    The value to validate.

    		 required

    Returns:

    Name Type Description
    Any Any

    The input value if it is not an empty string, otherwise None.

    @field_validator("*", mode="before")
@classmethod
def empty_str_to_none(cls, v: Any) -> Any:
    """Convert empty strings to None.

    TickTick API responses sometimes conflates `None` and empty strings for
    optional fields. This validator ensures that empty strings are converted to
    `None`, which then allows for more consistent handling of the data within the
    library.

    Args:
        v (Any): The value to validate.

    Returns:
        Any: The input value if it is not an empty string, otherwise `None`.
    """
    if isinstance(v, str) and len(v) == 0:
        return None
    return v

    @field_validator("*", mode="before")
@classmethod
def empty_str_to_none(cls, v: Any) -> Any:
    """Convert empty strings to None.

    TickTick API responses sometimes conflates `None` and empty strings for
    optional fields. This validator ensures that empty strings are converted to
    `None`, which then allows for more consistent handling of the data within the
    library.

    Args:
        v (Any): The value to validate.

    Returns:
        Any: The input value if it is not an empty string, otherwise `None`.
    """
    if isinstance(v, str) and len(v) == 0:
        return None
    return v

    `None`, which then allows for more consistent handling of the data within the
    library.

    Args:
        v (Any): The value to validate.

    Returns:
        Any: The input value if it is not an empty string, otherwise `None`.
    """
    if isinstance(v, str) and len(v) == 0:
        return None
    return v

    UpdateTaskV2 pydantic-model #

    Bases: BaseModelV2

    Model for updating a task via the V2 API.

    This model is used to update a task via the V2 API. It mostly maps to the 'items' field in the update task documentation. The main differences are the addition of the following fields:

    • modified_time
    • completed_time
    • completed_user_id
    • tags
    • etag
    • kind
    • status
    • is_floating
    • creator
    • assignee
    • progress

    This is used in the PostBatchTaskV2 model.

    empty_str_to_none(v: Any) -> Any

    Convert empty strings to None.

    TickTick API responses sometimes conflates None and empty strings for optional fields. This validator ensures that empty strings are converted to None, which then allows for more consistent handling of the data within the library.

    @field_validator("*", mode="before")
@classmethod
def empty_str_to_none(cls, v: Any) -> Any:
    """Convert empty strings to None.

    TickTick API responses sometimes conflates `None` and empty strings for
    optional fields. This validator ensures that empty strings are converted to
    `None`, which then allows for more consistent handling of the data within the
    library.

    Args:
        v (Any): The value to validate.

    Returns:
        Any: The input value if it is not an empty string, otherwise `None`.
    """
    if isinstance(v, str) and len(v) == 0:
        return None
    return v
